This native species is associated with Celtis L. spp. ( Cannabaceae ) ( Schoof 1942 ), specifically common hackberry, Celtis occidentalis L., in Quebec. All specimens collected in Montreal were beaten from common hackberry, and all those from Terrasse-Vaudreuil were attracted to a light source located no more than 10 m from a hackberry tree. Hackberry has been favoured as a street tree and planted in great numbers in some boroughs by the City of Montreal between 1972 and 1984 (
QueBio 2016
), obviously much to the benefit of the weevil. Records provided herein represent a significant northerly extension of the range of this species which was previously only known from as far north as Pennsylvania (
O'Brien and Wibmer 1982
).
